class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.html#Asymptotics.«term_=Θ[_;_]_»\"><span class=\"name\">Asymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_=Θ[_;_]_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that `f =Θ[𝕜; l] g` (`IsThetaTVS 𝕜 l f g`), if `f =O[𝕜; l] g` and `g =O[𝕜; l] f`.\nIt is a generalization of `f =Θ[l] g` that works in topological `𝕜`-vector spaces. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.html#Asymptotics.«term_=Θ[_;_]_»","kind":"def","line":123,"name":"Asymptotics.«term_=Θ[_;_]_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.lean#L123-L124"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.html#Asymptotics.IsThetaTVS\"><span class=\"name\">Asymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsThetaTVS</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#ENorm\">ENorm</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Zero\">Zero</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Zero\">Zero</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#SMul\">SMul</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#SMul\">SMul</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter\">Filter</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that `f =Θ[𝕜; l] g` (`IsThetaTVS 𝕜 l f g`), if `f =O[𝕜; l] g` and `g =O[𝕜; l] f`.\nIt is a generalization of `f =Θ[l] g` that works in topological `𝕜`-vector spaces. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.html#Asymptotics.IsThetaTVS","kind":"def","line":118,"name":"Asymptotics.IsThetaTVS","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.lean#L118-L121"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.html#Asymptotics.«term_=O[_;_]_»\"><span class=\"name\">Asymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_=O[_;_]_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`f =O[𝕜; l] g` (`IsBigOTVS 𝕜 l f g`) is a generalization of `f =O[l] g` (`IsBigO l f g`)\nthat works in topological `𝕜`-vector spaces.\n\nGiven two functions `f` and `g` taking values in topological vector spaces\nover a normed field `𝕜`,\nwe say that $f = O(g)$ if for any neighborhood of zero `U` in the codomain of `f`\nthere exists a neighborhood of zero `V` in the codomain of `g`\nsuch that $\\operatorname{gauge}_{K, U} (f(x)) \\le \\operatorname{gauge}_{K, V} (g(x))$,\nwhere $\\operatorname{gauge}_{K, U}(y) = \\inf \\{‖c‖ \\mid y ∈ c • U\\}$.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.html#Asymptotics.«term_=O[_;_]_»","kind":"def","line":115,"name":"Asymptotics.«term_=O[_;_]_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Asymptotics/TVS.lean#L115-L116"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_nam